    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00113 European War 1939/568: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-11">December 11,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6286. Your 6797, December 1. Your comments are requested regarding the
                    representation of this Government on the subcommittee of experts mentioned in
                    Section 2 of your reference telegram.</p>
                <p>If this work is to continue for some time, as seems likely, it might be desirable
                    to send an additional officer to the Legation who would have training in our
                    freezing controls and who could do other work in the Economic Warfare Division.
                    Another possibility, which we should like to discuss with Sommerville,<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d81fn9">James Somerville, First Secretary of Embassy at
                        London.</note> when he comes, would be to bring Robbins<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d81fn10">Albert H. Robbins, Senior Economic Analyst of Embassy at
                        London.</note> here for a period of training in our controls.</p>
                <p>Can you use somebody from your present staff on the subcommittee for the time
                    being (perhaps Spiegel<note n="11" xml:id="d81fn11">Harold R. Spiegel, Senior
                        Economic Analyst of Embassy at London.</note>) with the assistance of
                    information from here regarding the action we have taken to prevent Axis
                    countries from benefiting from forced transfers of property?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
